      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When you feel 100% better, that's a sign the treatment is working, but you still need to finish the full 10 days to be absolutely certain the infection is gone. If you stop early, you give the remaining tough bacteria a chance to survive and become resistant, which is a real problem. To be safe and truly eliminate the issue, stick to the full course, and if you're worried about your liver, just double-check that you're taking the correct dosage as prescribed.",
      "source": "target",
